  <prompt>
    Verify Wave 1 outputs are deploy-ready and consumable by downstream solutions. NO actual deployment in this task — surface deployments happen in Waves 3-5. This is a smoke-build pass.

    Steps:
    1. `@spaarke/ui-components` clean build: `npm run build` exits 0 with no errors / warnings.
    2. `@spaarke/ui-components` lint: `npm run lint` exits 0.
    3. `@spaarke/ui-components` tests: `npm run test` all green; coverage of `EmailComposer/` ≥ 80%.
    4. Bundle size delta vs pre-Wave-1 baseline: target ≤ +50 KB gzipped (engine + 4 source pickers + 3 wrappers + mode logic — reasonable budget per NFR-08).
    5. Public API surface audit: grep for `EmailComposer`, `SendEmailStep`, `SendEmailDialog`, `SendEmailPage`, `IComposerSourceRecord`, `IEmailComposerHandle`, etc. in the public barrel (`src/index.ts`). Confirm all expected exports.
    6. Downstream consumer smoke-builds — for each LIVE consumer of `@spaarke/ui-components`, run `npm run build`:
       - `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` (consumes SendEmailDialog via FilePreviewDialog — expect TS error at consumer post-task-022 wrapper rewrite; document the expected error; Wave 3 task 051 will fix)
       - `src/solutions/SummarizeFilesWizard/` (if it consumes lib)
       - Any other solutions importing the lib (audit `package.json` workspaces or grep `"@spaarke/ui-components"` in `dependencies`)
    7. Per FR-25 / NFR-07: confirm Form Component Control swap not yet attempted (Wave 2 handles); confirm standard form still default — no Dataverse changes in this task.
    8. Document: Wave 1 outputs ready for Wave 2 consumption.

    EXPECTED FAILURES — note in task notes:
    - `LegalWorkspace/.../FilePreviewDialog.tsx` will have a TS error (consuming the legacy `onSend` callback removed in task 022). Document; Wave 3 task 051 fixes.
    - Any consumers of `SendEmailStep` shared step that haven't migrated yet (Wave 5 task 071) — none expected (Wave 1 didn't change that file).

    OK to proceed if ONLY the expected failure above is the gap. Any other failure blocks Wave 2.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Build engineer / release coordinator comfortable with `npm run build` across a monorepo.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Wave 1 shared lib outputs build clean. Tests green + coverage ≥ 80%. Bundle size delta within budget. Consumer smoke-builds pass (modulo expected LegalWorkspace FilePreviewDialog TS error pending Wave 3 task 051). Wave 2 unblocked.
  </goal>

  <context>
