  <steps>
    <step order="1">In `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/`, run `npm run build` — must exit 0 with no warnings. Capture build output size (`dist/` size) for the bundle-delta comparison.</step>
    <step order="2">Run `npm run lint` — must exit 0.</step>
    <step order="3">Run `npm run test` — all suites green; coverage of `EmailComposer/` ≥ 80% lines.</step>
    <step order="4">Compute bundle delta: compare `dist/` total size vs pre-Wave-1 baseline (note baseline from git history at Wave 0 completion). Target: gzipped delta ≤ +50 KB.</step>
    <step order="5">Audit `src/index.ts` barrel — grep for expected exports: `EmailComposer`, `SendEmailStep`, `SendEmailDialog`, `SendEmailPage`, `IEmailComposerHandle`, `IEmailComposerProps`, `IComposerSourceRecord`, `IComposerAttachmentSource`, `IComposerAssociation`, `IRecipient`, `IAttachment`, `IValidationResult`, `EmailComposerMode`, `EmailComposerMount`, `EmailComposerValidationCode`, `SendCommunicationError`. Note any missing.</step>
    <step order="6">Audit downstream consumers — grep `"@spaarke/ui-components"` in all `package.json` files. For each consumer solution:
      - Run `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` (per CLAUDE.md §11 Vite solutions guidance)
      - Run `npm run build`
      - Capture output. Pass = clean build. Expected failure = LegalWorkspace/FilePreviewDialog.tsx (document).
    </step>
    <step order="7">Write summary report to PR description / task notes:
      - Shared lib: build ✅ / lint ✅ / test ✅ + coverage %
      - Bundle delta: +N KB gzipped (within ≤ +50 KB budget)
      - Public API surface: all expected exports present
      - Consumer smoke-builds: list each, pass/fail; document expected FilePreviewDialog failure
      - Conclusion: Wave 2 unblocked / blocked-on-X</step>
    <step order="8">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 029 ✅. Mark Wave 1 as complete.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol — advance to first Wave 2 task (030).</step>
  </steps>

